TYPHOID - PAPUA NEW GUINEA
**************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Typhoid - Papua New Guinea 980518064927
Date: Fri, 1 Jan 1999 13:20:54 -0800 (PST)
From: David Duffy <david_duffy@sprynet.com>
Source: Honolulu Advertiser 1 Jan 1999
Via: The Pacific Islands Development Program (University of Hawaii:
<http://pidp.ewc.hawaii.edu/PIReport>)

Mount Hagen, PNG. A doctor said roadside markets are to blame for
typhoid's rapidly becoming a common killer in the Highlands region. The 50
percent increase in the number of cases admitted to hospitals is the result
of people eating contaminated food and water from the markets, he said.
--
David Duffy
PCSU/Botany
University of Hawaii Manoa
e-mail: dduffy@hawaii.edu
